TITLE: Robinhood cutting about 23% of jobs, releases second-quarter earnings
SUMMARY: Robinhood CEO Vlad Tenev said Tuesday in a press release that the company will reduce its headcount by approximately 23%.

TITLE: AMD beats on earnings and revenue, but third-quarter forecast comes in light
SUMMARY: AMD currently has a significant market opportunity as its primary rival for PC and server chips, Intel, stumbles with execution.

TITLE: PayPal jumps as Elliott Management says it has a $2 billion holding in the financial services company
SUMMARY: PayPal stock has been cut in half in 2022, but it's getting a vote of confidence from hedge fund Elliott Management, which is also a big Pinterest investor.

TITLE: Starbucks earnings beat Wall Street estimates, fueled by U.S. demand for cold drinks
SUMMARY: Shares of Starbucks have fallen 27% this year, dragging its market value down to $98.37 billion.

TITLE: Airbnb stock slumps despite record-breaking bookings
SUMMARY: Airbnb's revenue jumped 58% year-over-year to $2.1 billion helping to drive the company’s most profitable second quarter to date.

TITLE: Ferrari boosts full-year guidance after a record second quarter
SUMMARY: Ferrari increased its full-year guidance after a quarter that set records for revenue, profit and new orders.

TITLE: JetBlue shares tumble as costs push it to a loss despite profit forecast on higher fares
SUMMARY: JetBlue posted a second-quarter loss and scaled back capacity growth plans.

TITLE: Uber reports another big loss but beats on revenue, shares pop 19%
SUMMARY: Uber reported a second quarter loss on Tuesday but beat analyst estimates for revenue.

TITLE: Oil major BP boosts dividend as quarterly profits jump on high commodity prices
SUMMARY: U.K. oil giant BP on Tuesday reported bumper second-quarter profits, benefitting from a surge in commodity prices.

TITLE: Pinterest climbs on user numbers and Elliott investment even as financials disappoint
SUMMARY: Pinterest shares jumped after the company's user numbers surpassed analysts' estimates in a gloomy quarter for social media.

TITLE: Chevron, Exxon post record quarterly profits as commodity prices boom
SUMMARY: Chevron and Exxon earned record profits during the second quarter of 2022.

TITLE: Higher prices help Procter & Gamble offset commodity costs, but Tide maker warns of more challenges
SUMMARY: Procter & Gamble reported mixed quarterly results and warned it expects challenges such as rising commodity costs to persist in its fiscal 2023.

TITLE: Roku shares crater after company misses on earnings and warns of 'recessionary fears'
SUMMARY: Roku shares plummeted more than 25% in extended trading on Thursday after the company missed expectations on the top and bottom lines for its second quarter.

TITLE: Intel CFO says we're 'on the bottom' after company misses earnings and stock sinks
SUMMARY: Consumers and schools aren't buying as many PCs as they were, driving a net loss for Intel. But price bumps in the fourth quarter should bolster margins.

TITLE: Apple beats on revenue and profit, expects growth to accelerate despite 'pockets of softness'
SUMMARY: Apple reported earnings on Thursday for its fiscal third quarter ending in June.

TITLE: Amazon jumps on revenue beat and rosy guidance for third quarter
SUMMARY: Amazon on Thursday reported second-quarter results that beat on the top line and issued rosy sales guidance for the third quarter.

TITLE: Pfizer quarterly sales surge to record high, driven by Covid vaccine and antiviral treatment Paxlovid
SUMMARY: The pharmaceutical company booked net income of $9.9 billion, a 78% increase over the same period during 2021.

TITLE: Comcast shares slide after the cable giant fails to add broadband subscribers for first time ever
SUMMARY: Comcast beat revenue and profit estimates but failed to deliver broadband subscriber growth. Peacock subscriber numbers were also flat.

TITLE: Barclays posts profit slump after hit from costly trading error in the U.S.
SUMMARY: Barclays took charges of £1.9 billion for the first half, including £1.3 billion related to its trading blunder in the U.S.

TITLE: Etsy shares pop as company beats on top and bottom lines
SUMMARY: Etsy shares jumped more than 15% in after-hours trading on Wednesday after the company's second quarter earnings beat on top and bottom lines.

TITLE: Meta reports earnings, revenue miss and forecasts second straight quarter of declining sales
SUMMARY: Meta's second-quarter earnings report comes after a 50% plunge in the company's stock price this year.

TITLE: Ford beats expectations and raises dividend as company sells more of its top models
SUMMARY: Ford reported second-quarter results that beat Wall Street's estimates for revenue and profit.

TITLE: Qualcomm sales rise 37% despite 'challenging macroeconomic environment'
SUMMARY: Qualcomm reported third-quarter earnings after the bell on Wednesday.

TITLE: Boeing sticks to 2022 cash flow forecast, prepares for Dreamliner deliveries to resume
SUMMARY: Boeing and Airbus has benefitted from a rebound in travel but supply chain and labor constraints are hindering output.

TITLE: Deutsche Bank beats expectations to post eighth straight quarter of profit
SUMMARY: Deutsche Bank beat market expectations to post an eighth straight quarter of profit on Wednesday, recording a second-quarter net income of 1.046 billion euros ($1.06 billion).

TITLE: Credit Suisse names Ulrich Koerner as CEO, launches strategic review as losses deepen
SUMMARY: The embattled Swiss bank posted a net loss of 1.593 billion Swiss francs ($1.66 billion), far below consensus expectations among analysts for a 398.16 million Swiss franc loss.

TITLE: Enphase sees strong solar growth in Europe as natural gas prices soar
SUMMARY: Europe's energy crisis is prompting consumers to go solar, which is lifting Enphase's operations.

TITLE: YouTube has 'obvious math' problem as growth slows dramatically from pandemic highs
SUMMARY: Alphabet executives blamed tough comparisons and economic challenges for YouTube's slowing growth rate.

TITLE: Microsoft misses estimates but stock up 5% on rosy guidance
SUMMARY: Microsoft said it would have had more revenue in the quarter were it not for unfavorable foreign-exchange rates and tougher PC and advertising markets.

TITLE: Alphabet misses on earnings and revenue for second quarter
SUMMARY: Alphabet reported earnings after the bell. Here are the results.
